-- AXA Equitable Names E*Trade’s Radin Chief Marketing Officer
-- B y   A n d r e a   L u d t k e
-- 2012-02-13T19:23:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-13/axa-equitable-names-e-trade-s-radin-as-chief-marketing-officer.html
AXA Equitable  Life Insurance 
Co., the seller of life insurance and retirement annuity
products, named Amy Radin to the new position of senior
executive vice president and chief marketing officer.  Radin, former chief innovation officer at E*Trade Financial
Corp., reports to Mark Pearson, chairman and chief executive
officer, the New York-based insurer said today in a statement
distributed by PR Newswire. Radin has also led marketing,
digital and customer service initiatives at Reader’s Digest
Association Inc. and spent nine years at  Citigroup Inc. (C)   “Marketing and communications are central to our plans to
build the AXA Equitable brand around the customer experience,”
Pearson said in the statement. “Amy clearly brings a wealth of
expertise to this effort, along with a track record of success
in customer-focused initiatives throughout her career.”  AXA Equitable is owned by Paris-based  Axa SA (CS) , France’s
biggest insurer and No. 2 in  Europe  behind Allianz SE. Axa, led
by Chief Executive Officer Henri de Castries, is scheduled to
announce full-year results this week.  Axa rose less than 1 percent to 12.42 euros today in Paris.
It has fallen 21 percent in the past 12 months.  To contact the reporter on this story:
